WHEREAS the Convention concerning the Creation of an

International Office of Weights and Measures (hereinafter referred to as "the Convention") was done at Paris on 20 May 1875, and was amended at Sevres on 6 October 1921;

AND WHEREAS any State may adhere to the Convention;

AND WHEREAS pursuant to Article 3 of the 1921 Convention, any adhesions to the Convention shall automatically entail adherence to the 1921 Convention;

NOW THEREFORE the Government Of New Zealand, having considered the Convention, HEREBY ADHERES to the same and undertakes faithfully to observe its provisions and all the stipulations therein contained.

IN WITNESS THEREOF I have signed this Instrument of

Adherence and have affixed hereto the seal of the Minister of Foreign Affairs of New Zealand.

DATED at Wellington this

q* day of May 1991,

Acting Minister of Foreign Affairs
